<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Any sufficiently advanced technology is indistinguishable from magic.&quot; -- Arthur C. Clarke <br>
<br>
&quot;Any sufficiently advanced extraterrestrial intelligence is indistinguishable from God&quot;  -- Scientific American: Skeptic : Shermer's Last Law: January 2002 By MICHAEL SHERMER </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dustyslaunchpad>Dustys Launchpad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NEP Freighter Crewman</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(2/10/03 5:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/fry1.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re Space aliens</span><hr size=1> I’ve always favoured the idea of an island-based civilisation, existing during the last ice age, providing the foundation for many of these myths and legends rather than visits by space aliens. I think we tend to underestimate our forefathers potential capabilities. <br>
<br>
15-20,000 year’s ago; an isolated, highly advanced, island civilisation could have achieved a degree of sophistication equal to 19th century Britain, (possibly even 20th century). If it was subsequently destroyed by some natural catastrophe such as vulcanism (or rising sea levels at the end of the ice-age) there could easily be no trace left today apart from the odd legend. (Atlantis?)<br>
<br>
We know (?<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) that nobody has developed (Large-scale) space flight before; a geo-stationary satellite would still be there after 20,000 years. We also know that there was no large scale, technically sophisticated, civilisation (Otherwise we would have evidence of mineral extraction) but a small island civilisation is a different matter, especially one that didn’t last that long.<br>
<br>
Dusty<br>
<br>
